{
  "name": "refactor-travel-segment-20260413-2020",
  "idea": "Refactor travel segment guidance positioning to compute stitched_start_frame at task creation time instead of having the worker reconstruct it from segment_frames_expanded arrays. The worker should read a single pre-computed field instead of receiving full pipeline layout arrays and recomputing position. This eliminates the entire class of bugs we just hit (4 commits to fix a missing array that shouldn't have been needed). Key files: reigh-worker/source/task_handlers/travel/guide_builder.py (consumer), reigh-worker/source/media/structure/segments.py (calculation), reigh-app/supabase/functions/create-task/resolvers/individualTravelSegment.ts (frontend segment creation), reigh-app/supabase/functions/create-task/resolvers/travelBetweenImages.ts (orchestrator segment creation).",
